A 34-year-old civil servant, Iweha Nwabueze, who al­legedly attacked a woman during a party, appeared in a Wuse Zone 6 Magistrates’ Court in Abuja. Nwabueze, who resides in Lugbe,
Abuja, is charged with two counts of crimi­nal intimidation and caus­ing
grievous hurt. The prosecution coun­sel, Peter
Ejike, told the court that the defendant committed the offence on Nov.30, 2019 Powered by RubiQube Ad Network He alleged that on Dec. 9, the
complainant, Ms Temi­tope Adewusi, who resides in Garki, Abuja reported the
matter at the Wuse Zone 3 Police Station. He alleged that the de­fendant
attacked the com­plainant with an object and injured her on her lower lip at
Graceland Garden in Wuse Zone 4, during an end of year function, without any
provocation. In addition, the prosecu­tor
alleged that the defen­dant also threatened to deal with her. The prosecutor said the offence
contravened the provisions of sections 397 and 242 of the penal code. The defendant, however, pleaded
not guilty. The Chief Magistrate, Linda
Chidama, admitted the defendant to bail in the sum of N400, 000 with one surety
in like sum. She adjourned the case until Feb. 12 for hearing.